{{Frame
|Program alias=ELECTIONS
|Comments=An election is a decision-making process using VOTING to decide on the identity of an official office-holder in some Institution (often a Government Institution). The Voters are members (adult members...) of the governed population of the relevant Government Institution. Normally there are multiple (at least two) Candidates for an Office. The Outcome of the Voting is a decision about the identity of the office-holder who will fill that institutional function. 
So links to Institution, Government Institution, and Voting, for sure.
